#Text=Chinese premier Wen Jiabao visits Shakespeare 's birthplace
#Text=Monday , June 27 , 2011
#Text=Premier Jiabao Image : World Economic Forum .
#Text=Chinese premier
#Text=Wen Jiabao paid a visit to the birthplace of English playwright and poet William Shakespeare on Sunday .
#Text=The visit to Stratford-upon-Avon was included in his three-day tour of various industries in Britain .
#Text=The UK is one of China 's biggest trading partners , second only to the EU .
#Text=[ Stratford-upon-Avon ] has produced a figure who belongs not only to the UK but to the world .
#Text=A great man who belongs not just to his era but to entire history .
#Text=— Premier Wen Jiabao
#Text=The 68-year-old Wen , reportedly a fan of Shakespeare , was met upon his arrival at Stratford-upon-Avon by dozens of flag-waving individuals from the UK 's Chinese community .
#Text=He visited Shakespeare 's birthplace , which is now a museum and then attended a scene from Shakespeare 's " Hamlet " , his favourite play , while sitting in the " sun-drenched " garden .
#Text=He toured the collection of treasures at the town 's Shakespeare Birthplace Trust .
#Text=On his tour at the Trust , lasting half an hour longer than planned , he looked through a 17th-century folio of Shakespeare 's famous plays .
#Text=Trust director Diana Owen , who talked with Wen during his informal tour , said Wen described Shakespeare as " the greatest writer of all time .

#Text=There were several protesters outside Downing Street , who held a banner that read  Cameron and Wen : human rights before trade " .

column1: #Text=The goal of the visit , part of a three-nation tour of Europe , is the strengthening of economic ties between the two countries .
#Text=China is increasingly outsourcing its own manufacturing to less costly labour markets and wants to increase its investments in established European brands .
#Text=Today , China and Britain announced contracts worth over one billion pounds .
#Text=John Shakespeare 's house , believed to be Shakespeare 's birthplace , in Stratford-upon-Avon .

#Text=I am hoping that a billion Chinese might see some pictures on their TV of their premier coming and visiting the birthplace of Shakespeare , and thinking : ' Well , I 'd like to go there as well . ' — Jeremy Hunt , British Culture Secretary
#Text=British Culture Secretary Jeremy Hunt , whose wife is Chinese , was hopeful that Wen 's visit would have a positive effect on the country 's tourism industry .

#Text=He told Sky News , " I am hoping that a billion Chinese might see some pictures on their TV of their premier coming and visiting the birthplace of Shakespeare , and thinking : ' Well , I 'd like to go there as well .
